So, are intelligence tests reliable and valid?

1
00:00:10,670 --> 00:00:13,790
Intelligence tests are some of the most reliable tests that we have.

2
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:18,560
It was the intelligence movement that really focused on the psychometric properties of

3
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:23,679
tests, and so there&#39;s been a very clear focus on improving the reliability of tests.

4
00:00:23,679 --> 00:00:28,331
When you look at the correlation between scores people receive on intelligence tests at two

5
00:00:28,331 --> 00:00:35,440
different times, test-retest reliability, the average correlation is around 0.85.

6
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:39,710
It can be higher, but 0.85 is the average correlation.

7
00:00:39,710 --> 00:00:43,870
For a range of different tests, having an average correlation of 0.85 would generally

8
